ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I have a much clearer picture. Let me analyze the key issues:\n\n
1. **The existing step definition files load DIFFERENT feature files**:\n   - `m
atching_card_recommendations.steps.js` loads `../matching_card_recommendations.f
eature`\n   - `matching_swipe_actions.steps.js` loads `../matching_swipe_actions
.feature`\n   - etc.\n\nBut the NEW `matching.steps.js` loads `../matching.featu
re`!\n\nSo there are TWO sets of feature files:\n- Individual feature files: `ma
tching_card_recommendations.feature`, `matching_swipe_actions.feature`, etc.\n- 
Consolidated feature file: `matching.feature`\n\nThe PR modifies `matching.featu
re` and adds `matching.steps.js` for it. The existing step definitions are for t
he INDIVIDUAL feature files.\n\nThis means:\n- The consolidated `matching.featur
e` was likely NOT being tested before (no step definitions for it)\n- The PR add
s step definitions for the consolidated `matching.feature`\n- The individual fea
ture files still have their own step definitions\n\nSo there\'s no direct confli
ct! They\'re for different feature files.\n\nBut wait - are the individual featu
re files and the consolidated feature file both being matched by Jest? Let me ch
eck the jest config again.\n\n`testMatch: [\'<rootDir>/tests/bdd/step-definition
s/*.steps.js\']` - this matches ALL step definition files. So:\n- `matching_card
_recommendations.steps.js` runs `matching_card_recommendations.feature`\n- `matc
hing_swipe_actions.steps.js` runs `matching_swipe_actions.feature`\n- `matching.
steps.js` runs `matching.feature`\n\nAll three would run. If the consolidated `m
atching.feature` contains the SAME scenarios as the individual feature files, th
en the same scenarios are tested twice. But that\'s not a "failure" - it\'s just
duplicate coverage.\n\nHowever, looking at the existing step definition files, t
hey use different Given/When/Then text from what the new `matching.steps.js` use
s. For example:\n- Old: `given(\'the user is on the home screen with a complete 
profile\', ...)`\n- New: `given(\'Alice has a complete profile with location\', 
...)`\n\nThis means the individual feature files (`matching_card_recommendations
.feature`) use different scenario text from the consolidated `matching.feature`.
Let me verify this.\n\nActually, I don\'t have the individual feature files. Let
me check if they exist.',
    encrypted=None
)
